sub_title: Field Service Engineer at ProfiNRG (Solar PV System & Energy Storage)
summary:
-My name is Habip Ceylan and I graduated from Mehmet Akif Ersoy University Energy Systems Engineering undergraduate education in 2021 with a 3.00 GPA. 


-I studied at two particular universities through the exchange program, Polytechnic University of Lodz and State University of Applied Sciences in Pila for 2 semesters in total. I got a lot of experience from important lessons such as fluid mechanics and electric machines I took during the program, moreover; I developed projects by collaborating with people of different nations and easily adapted to groups. 


-During the exchange program in Poland, I also worked as an engineer intern at Phillips Electrical company. Since I worked in the production department, my duties were generally monitoring performance of the products on daily basis and providing control over WinCC. On the other hand, in Turkey I worked as an intern at the wind and solar power plant of a company called VEGA Energy for about 2 months. During my internship, I gained skills in electrical works in the field (Transformer, Converter, Generator...), manufacturing process and wind and solar energy project management. I mostly established energy projects, especially solar module projects on sites via using PvSyst and also reported daily-basis status. I participated in leading companies in the wind and solar sectors, such as Enercon and CW Energy and learned about the production of blades and nacelle parts and the PV modules.
